The paper deals with fundamental graph parameters and algorithms for computing them, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of All-Pairs Shortest Paths and the study of distance measures also suggest that it could belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The study of distances and paths in graphs is a classic topic in Discrete Mathematics, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely sub-category. The use of approximation algorithms and time/accuracy trade-offs suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the study of graph parameters and optimization problems could also place the paper in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
